      "content": "important major information",
      "contentHtml": null
    },
    {
      "id": "4ae56f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralText",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 3,
      "content": "PREPARATION FOR TRANSFER AT THE JUNIOR LEVEL Courses indicated are articulated to a minimum equivalent in the Berkeley German program. Students may actually be placed higher by the Language Program Coordinator. In order to declare the major, students may be required, at the discretion of the Coordinator, to take the fourth semester course at Berkeley and receive a passing grade. For information about placement at Berkeley contact: Maxwell Moloney Department of German Phone: 510-642-7445 germanua@berkeley.edu http://german.berkeley.edu/",
      "contentHtml": "<p><strong>PREPARATION FOR TRANSFER AT THE JUNIOR LEVEL </strong></p><p><br></p><p>Courses indicated are articulated to a <strong>minimum </strong>equivalent in the Berkeley German program. Students may actually be placed higher by the Language Program Coordinator. In order to declare the major, students may be required, at the discretion of the Coordinator, to take the fourth semester course at Berkeley and receive a passing grade.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>For information about placement at Berkeley contact: </strong></p><p>Maxwell Moloney</p><p>Department of German</p><p>Phone: 510-642-7445</p><p><a href=\"mailto:germanua@berkeley.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">germanua@berkeley.edu</a></p><p><a href=\"http://germanic@berkeley.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"> </a><a href=\"http://german.berkeley.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">http://german.berkeley.edu/</a></p>"
    }
